author: Nuran Alteir | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Report: Girl, mom found safe after Yakima police issue Amber Alert
text:
Police say a 3-year-old girl and her mom were found safe Tuesday after authorities issued an Amber Alert stating they had been abducted, the Yakima Herald reports .
Kyle Arellano, 18, has been identified as a suspect in the disappearance of 3-year-old Lupita Tellez and her mother Vivianna Cruz. Washington State Police Lupita Tellez, 3, and her mother Vivianna Cruz were reported missing at about 6 p.m. Yakima police said the two were forced into a vehicle at about 10:15 a.m. on Tuesday, according to the Amber Alert , which has been canceled after they were found safe in Spokane.
The suspect, 18-year-old Kyle Arellano, remains at large, Yakima police spokesman Mike Bastinelli told the Yakima Herald. He is described as an 18-year-old man weighing 260 pounds and is 6 feet 3 inches tall. Police believe he may be driving a silver 2000 Mitsubishi Galant with the license plate No. AUP4936.
Anyone with information about this case is asked to call Washington State Police at 509-575-2320 .
